repository-code: >-
  https://github.com/DiegoFernandoLojanTenesaca/TIC_Analisis_Sentimientos_SVM_OPTUNA
abstract: >-
  Code and experiments accompanying a study on stress detection
  in Spanish social media text during the 2024 Ecuadorian
  energy crisis. The work applies Bayesian hyperparameter
  optimization (Tree-structured Parzen Estimator via Optuna)
  to Support Vector Machines, combined with FastText Skip-gram
  embeddings and SMOTE balancing, following the CRISP-DM
  methodology. Evaluated on 26,600 ethically scraped tweets
  and 18,515 messages from the MentalRiskES corpus, the
  optimized model reaches F1-scores of 92.60% (Twitter/X) and
  97.23% (MentalRiskES), with a 62% reduction in false
  negatives on MentalRiskES.
keywords:
  - sentiment analysis
  - affective computing
  - support vector machines
  - bayesian optimization
  - tree-structured parzen estimator
  - optuna
  - fasttext
  - smote
  - crisp-dm
  - spanish nlp
  - mental health
  - stress detection
  - ecuadorian energy crisis
